## Entry Points
- **Main**: `openclaw.mjs` — CLI entry point and gateway launcher
- **Gateway**: `src/gateway/server.ts` — Core gateway server
- **Agent**: `src/agents/agent-runner.ts` — Agent spawning and management
- **CLI**: `src/cli/run-main.js` — Command-line interface handler
- **Tests**: `pnpm test` — Run test suite via vitest

## Key Concepts
- **Gateway**: Central server coordinating all agent interactions
- **Agents**: Independent AI instances with unique sessions and capabilities
- **Extensions**: Modular enhancements providing specialized functionality
- **Memory**: Persistent storage with embeddings for semantic search
- **Channels**: Communication interfaces (Signal, WhatsApp, Discord, etc.)
- **Tools**: MCP-compatible tool implementations for external interactions
- **Sessions**: Isolated conversation contexts with state management
- **Nodes**: Paired devices for distributed operation

## Dependencies
- **Runtime**: Node.js 22+, TypeScript 5.5+, pnpm workspace
- **Database**: SQLite with WAL mode, sqlite-vec extension
- **AI Models**: Anthropic Claude, OpenAI GPT, Google Gemini
- **Browser**: Chrome with custom extension, Playwright
- **Messaging**: signal-cli, whatsapp-web.js
- **Dev**: Vitest, ESLint, Prettier, Oxlint

